Good — now that collaborators are added, follow this *exact execution order* for your *3-member team (TL, M1, M2)*.

This covers: *clone → branch → commit → merge conflict → rebase → cleanup*.

---

# PART 1 — MEMBERS CLONE (M1, M2)

Each member runs:

bash
git clone git@github.com:PrabhaB1210/seven-wonders.git
cd seven-wonders


---

# PART 2 — CREATE BRANCHES

### Team Lead

bash
git checkout -b wonder-tl


### Member 1

bash
git checkout -b wonder-m1


### Member 2

bash
git checkout -b wonder-m2


---

# PART 3 — ADD FILES + COMMIT + PUSH

### Team Lead

bash
echo "Machu Picchu" > wonder-tl.txt
git add .
git commit -m "TL added wonder"
git push -u origin wonder-tl


### Member 1

bash
echo "Great Wall" > wonder-m1.txt
git add .
git commit -m "M1 added wonder"
git push -u origin wonder-m1


### Member 2

bash
echo "Taj Mahal" > wonder-m2.txt
git add .
git commit -m "M2 added wonder"
git push -u origin wonder-m2


---

# PART 4 — MERGE CONFLICT PRACTICE

### Team Lead edits main

bash
git checkout main
git pull
echo "Edited by TL" >> wonders.txt
git add .
git commit -m "TL edited file"
git push


### Members edit SAME file (important to create conflict)

Member 1

bash
git checkout wonder-m1
echo "Edited by M1" >> wonders.txt
git add .
git commit -m "M1 edit"
git push


Member 2

bash
git checkout wonder-m2
echo "Edited by M2" >> wonders.txt
git add .
git commit -m "M2 edit"
git push


---

# PART 5 — TEAM LEAD MERGES BRANCHES

bash
git checkout main
git merge wonder-m1


Conflict appears → open wonders.txt → fix → then:

bash
git add wonders.txt
git commit -m "Conflict resolved"
git push


Repeat:

bash
git merge wonder-m2


Resolve → commit → push

---

# PART 6 — REBASE (MEMBERS)

Member 1

bash
git checkout wonder-m1
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/main


Member 2

bash
git checkout wonder-m2
git fetch origin
git rebase origin/main


---

# PART 7 — CLEANUP

### Team Lead deletes remote branches

bash
git push origin --delete wonder-m1
git push origin --delete wonder-m2
git push origin --delete wonder-tl


### Members delete local branches

bash
git branch -d wonder-m1
git branch -d wonder-m2


---

# Very important memory shortcut (exam)

Always remember the workflow:


Clone
→ Branch
→ Commit
→ Push
→ Merge
→ Conflict resolve
→ Rebase
→ Cleanup


